Q2. How do you plan on deploying this to the production environment?
Ans.  1. Choose Heroku a hosting provider.
      2. Set up a production-ready server with a WSGI serverand a web server.
      3. Configure a production database(MySQL or PostgreSQL) and set necessary environment variables.
      4. Set SSL/TLS certificates for secure communication.
      5. Use a process manager to keep your application running.
      6. Automate deployment using tools like Ansible or Docker for consistency.
      7. Implement continuous integration and continuous deployment (CI/CD) pipelines.
      8. Regularly update dependencies and apply security patches.
      9. Implement monitoring and logging for performance and error tracking.
      10 Regularly back up your database and media files.
